Package ohos.bundle

Class ElementName

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.bundle.ElementName
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sequenceable

    public class ElementName
extends Object
implements Sequenceable
    Contains basic Ability information, which uniquely identifies an ability.

    You can use this class to obtain values of the fields set in an element, such as the device ID, bundle name, and ability name.

    Since:
    1

      • createRelative

        public static ElementName createRelative​(String bundleName,
                                         String abilityName,
                                         String deviceId)
        Creates another ElementName instance where the class name of the ability is prefixed with the package name.
        Parameters:
        bundleName - Indicates the name of the bundle to which the specified ability belongs. This parameter cannot be null.
        abilityName - Indicates the class name of the ability. This parameter cannot be null.
        deviceId - Indicates the ID of the device running the specified ability.
        Returns:
        Returns the created ElementName instance.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if abilityName is null or an empty string.
        Since:
        3

      • getShortClassName

        public String getShortClassName​()
        Obtains the short class name of the ability in the current ElementName instance.

        The short class name is not prefixed with the package name. Instead, it starts with a period (.), for example, .MainAbility.

        Returns:
        Returns the short class name of the ability in the current ElementName instance.
        Since:
        3

      • unflattenFromString

        public static ElementName unflattenFromString​(String elementName)
        Restores an ElementName instance from the string created using getURI().

        The string must be in the format deviceId/bundleName/abilityName, for example, deviceId1/com.abc.hiword/com.abc.hiword.MainAbility.

        Parameters:
        elementName - Indicates the string representing the element name, which is obtained from getURI(). This parameter cannot be null.
        Returns:
        Returns an ElementName instance.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if elementName is null or is not in the specified format.
        Since:
        3
